 ECT  In addition to on site activities  clerkship didactics include a core lecture series  and the Tuesday Morning Seminar where students research and present a mental health topic for discussion The fundamentals of patient interviewing  diagnosis and risk assessment are emphasized throughout this rotation with the expectation that students will develop competency in these areas  Students are also introduced to commonly utilized psychiatric treatment modalities such as pharmacotherapy  as well as a variety of individual and group psychotherapies Education MD Admissions Rockford Interviews MD Curriculum Campus Specific Programs Clinician Executive Medicine Program  CE MED James Scholar Program for Independent Study Rural Medical Education  RMED  Program Curriculum by Year M  Year M  Year M  and M  Years Psychiatry Clerkship Course Management Blackboard Exams Benware Course Evaluations Visiting Students Medical Education and Evaluation MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Staff Academic Skills Step   Resources Housing Computing Registrar Career Services Scholarship Opportunities Student Financial Planning Student Health and Wellness MD Student Life Rockford Resources Student Organizations Parking   Transportation Diversity Educational Policies Master of Science in Medical Biotechnology Program Master of Science in Medical Biotechnology Program Start a Career Through the MBT Program Admissions Information and Requirements FAQs Guaranteed Admission Program Agreement Curriculum Overview Tuition and Fees Contact Information MBT Contact Me Form MBT Faculty and Staff MBT Photo Gallery Testimonials Graduate Medical Education  GME Family Medicine Residency Welcome Where are our graduates now  Policies Manual Career and Life Planning for Residents Rockford Family Medicine Residency Program Curriculum First Year Residency Second Year Residency Third Year Residency Salary Benefits Resident Life SwedishAmerican Hospital How to Apply Our Faculty Visit us on Facebook Fa